games.comment: Brent Celek, who had 6 receptions for 131 yards in relief of L.J. Smith. Jackson had 2 catches for 20 yards.

Brent Celek to operate as the long snapper for a field goal. Celek had a poor snap on what was a missed field goal, and then was injured on a punt. After that, another tight end, Trey Burton, played the position. He executed on the 1 field goal he snapped for. It was a pretty interesting storyline from what was an exciting NFC East battle.    Final Note: The Redskins may have lost 2 of their top middle linebackers this week.
